-- Saudi Southern Province Cement Falls Most in Two Months After Profit Drops
-- Mourad Haroutunian
-- 2010-07-17T12:03:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/saudi-southern-province-cement-falls-most-in-two-months-after-profit-drops.html

          
          
             Southern Province Cement Co. , the
largest cement producer in Saudi Arabia, fell the most in almost
two months in Riyadh trading after reported a 13 percent drop in
second-quarter profit.  
 The shares dropped as much as 4.4 percent to 66 riyals, the
biggest decline in intraday trading since May 22. Net income
fell to 185 million riyals ($49 million) from 212 million riyals
a year earlier on lower sales, the company said.  
 Farouk Miah , equity analyst at NCB Capital, had estimated
that earnings amounted to 201 million riyals.  
